Grill maker Weber-Stephen sells majority stake to BDT Capital


(Crain's) — BDT Capital Partners LLC, an investment group led by Chicago investment banker Byron Trott, has purchased a majority stake in Weber-Stephen Products Co., the Palatine-based maker of Weber grills.Chicago-based BDT is acquiring the stake by way of a partnership with the Stephen family, which founded the privately held company in 1952. Financial terms of the transaction, including the size of the stake, weren’t disclosed. The transaction is expected to close this month.“We are excited to partner with the Stephen family and the Weber management team to continue to build upon the strength of the business in the U.S., Europe and Australia and grow the brand in other key markets around the world,” Mr. Trott said in a news release. Mr. Trott is the managing partner and chief investment officer for BDT, which offers long-term capital and advisory services to its family business clients. His investment fund has about $2 billion under management and is connected to an investor base willing to contribute additional capital.  “This partnership with BDT Capital Partners allows us to continue to invest in the business, produce innovative high-quality products, deliver strong customer service, and build upon the global strength and heritage of the Weber brand,” James Stephen, the second-generation president and CEO of the family-owned company, said in the release.The Stephen family plans to retain ownership of its four Weber-branded restaurants.


Byron D. Trott
Mergers and Acquisitions



























